<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="203" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1127,727,1104]" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,251,920,944]" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">Remark.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="NEL J." box="[257,376,920,944]" pageId="6" pageNumber="203" pagination="1 - 61" refId="ref5585" refString="NEL J. 2003: Atlas des Lepidopteres Pterophoridae de France. Revue de l'Association Roussillonnaise d'Entomologie 12 (Suppl.): 1 - 61." type="journal article" year="2003">NEL (2003)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="ARENBERGER E." box="[424,632,919,944]" pageId="6" pageNumber="203" refId="ref4880" refString="ARENBERGER E. 2005: Pterophoridae III (Platyptiliini, Stenoptilia). In: GAEDIKE R. (ed.): Microlepidoptera Palaearctica. Vol. 12. Goecke &amp; Evers, Keltern, 191 pp." type="book" year="2005">ARENBERGER (2005)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bigot &amp; Picard" authorityYear="2002" box="[758,923,921,944]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Stenoptilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mariaeluisae">
<emphasis box="[758,923,921,944]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">S. mariaeluisae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a valid species and 
<bibRefCitation author="ARENBERGER E." box="[151,360,951,976]" pageId="6" pageNumber="203" refId="ref4880" refString="ARENBERGER E. 2005: Pterophoridae III (Platyptiliini, Stenoptilia). In: GAEDIKE R. (ed.): Microlepidoptera Palaearctica. Vol. 12. Goecke &amp; Evers, Keltern, 191 pp." type="book" year="2005">ARENBERGER (2005)</bibRefCitation>
found it in 
<collectingRegion box="[486,545,951,975]" country="Italy" name="Friuli-Venezia Giulia" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">Friuli</collectingRegion>
Venezia Giulia and 
<collectingRegion box="[763,844,951,975]" country="Italy" name="Lazio" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">Latium</collectingRegion>
. On the other hand, 
<bibRefCitation author="GIELIS C." pageId="6" pageNumber="203" refId="ref5176" refString="GIELIS C. 2003: Pterophoridea &amp; Alucitoidea (Lepidoptera). In: VAN DER WOLF H. (ed.): World Catalogue of Insects. Vol. 4. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 198 pp." type="book" year="2003">GIELIS (2003)</bibRefCitation>
considers it a synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zeller" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[507,591,985,1008]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Stenoptilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arida">
<emphasis box="[507,591,985,1008]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">S. arida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As stated above, all records of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zeller" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[929,1013,985,1008]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Stenoptilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arida">
<emphasis box="[929,1013,985,1008]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">S. arida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1077,1126,983,1007]" name="Italy" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">Italy</collectingCountry>
should be checked. Our findings confirm the presence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bigot &amp; Picard" authorityYear="2002" box="[758,923,1017,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Stenoptilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mariaeluisae">
<emphasis box="[758,923,1017,1040]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">S. mariaeluisae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[957,1023,1015,1039]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">Sicily</collectingRegion>
; the characters of male and female genitalia are identical to those described by 
<bibRefCitation author="BIGOT L. &amp; PICARD J." box="[884,1126,1048,1072]" pageId="6" pageNumber="203" pagination="301 - 311" refId="ref5052" refString="BIGOT L. &amp; PICARD J. 2002: Les Stenoptilia de la section grisescens en France. Stenoptilia mariaeluisae nov. sp. et Stenoptilia inopinata nov. sp. Alexanor 21 (5) (2000): 301 - 311." type="journal article" year="2002">BIGOT &amp; PICARD (2002)</bibRefCitation>
for the 
<typeStatus box="[228,321,1079,1103]" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">holotype</typeStatus>
and the 
<typeStatus box="[413,502,1079,1103]" pageId="6" pageNumber="203">allotype</typeStatus>
; see also 
<bibRefCitation author="NEL J." box="[603,723,1080,1104]" pageId="6" pageNumber="203" pagination="1 - 61" refId="ref5585" refString="NEL J. 2003: Atlas des Lepidopteres Pterophoridae de France. Revue de l'Association Roussillonnaise d'Entomologie 12 (Suppl.): 1 - 61." type="journal article" year="2003">NEL (2003)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="ARENBERGER E." box="[773,984,1079,1104]" pageId="6" pageNumber="203" refId="ref4880" refString="ARENBERGER E. 2005: Pterophoridae III (Platyptiliini, Stenoptilia). In: GAEDIKE R. (ed.): Microlepidoptera Palaearctica. Vol. 12. Goecke &amp; Evers, Keltern, 191 pp." type="book" year="2005">ARENBERGER (2005)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
